node.text:
Here’s the recipe for the keto vanilla birthday cake I made with Ube cream cheese frosting! This was a fun experiment. I was genuinely surprised by how moist and fluffy the cake came out! BTW, definitely also had “real” cake...and milkshakes...and bread pudding too cuz...there’s no holding back on your birthday!!!

Cake ingredients: 

3 c almond flour
1 c coconut flour
4 tsp baking powder
1/2 tsp salt
1.5 c vegan butter, softened
1.5 c monkfruit sugar
8 eggs
1 c almond milk
2 tsp vanilla extract

Ube cream cheese frosting ingredients:

1 c monkfruit powdered sugar
16 oz vegan cream cheese, softened
1/2 c softened vegan butter
1/2 tsp of ube extract

Method:

1. Mix all cake ingredients together
2. Bake for 45 min - 1 hr depending on your oven, until firm on top, at 350 F
3. Once firm, remove from oven, let cool, then slice into 2 or 3 layers
4. For frosting, whip all ingredients together, then chill in fridge
5. Once both the cake and frosting are cool, add frosting between each layer of cake, and then on the outside
6. Slice and enjoy!

Makes 16 servings!

Recipe adapted from @thebigmansworld keto birthday cake.

I wanted to see once and for all what simple 2-3 ingredient healthy cookie recipe would taste the best! So, I put 5 recipes against each other!

1.5 banana + 1/2 c coconut flour

1 banana + 1/2 c rolled oats

1.5 banana + 1/2 c pea protein

1 banana + 1/2 c dessicated coconut

1 banana + 1/2 c dessicated coconut + 1/2 c peanut powder

Watch the video to find which recipe failed and which recipe won! I’m always looking for an easy staple healthy cookie recipe...which do you wanna try?

node.text:
I love dancing! It is my favorite form of cardio because it never feels like cardio, you know what I mean?! I'm sad that I can't take dance classes or fitness classes right now, but it's all good because we need to do our part to flatten the curve! And that means social distancing!
.
Anyway, my friend @thefitnessmarshall tagged me in the Your Turn Dance Challenge and I was like nooooo SO MUCH CHOREO TO LEARN but once I got started it wasn't that bad. Thank you Caleb for the lil push :) I had a lot of fun getting my groove on, so if you guys wanna learn it too, just follow my tutorial! I tacked on the last 4 counts and YES IT INCLUDES A HAIR WHIP YOU ARE VERY WELCOME.
.
Here's how this all got started BTW!
.
1️⃣Started by @daniellenatoni - this challenge is designed to see how much choreography we can build by each person adding 4 counts at a time!
2️⃣Danielle then threw it to @officialtaniabaron who did her 4 counts who then threw it to @shaunt who threw it to @drlaurenfitz who thew it to @thefitnessmarshall who has now thrown it to me!
3️⃣I added on my own 4 counts inspired by my heels classes and NOW I CHALLENGE MY LIL SISTER @jackelynho to add the next 4 counts!
4️⃣Who will be next and how long will this keep going?!?😍🙌🏼🤷🏼‍♀️
#yourturndancechallenge #dance #dancechallenge #socialdistancing

node.text:
I used to get upset thinking why women had to be the ones to endure all the pain of pregnancy, childbirth, and post pregnancy while men had it easy.

Whenever @samlivits asked if it was time for us to have a baby, I kept joking, “yeah, anytime if humans could be like seahorses!”

Fun fact: With seahorses, the sperm-producers are also the ones that get pregnant!!! The female transfers her eggs to the male’s abdominal pouch and the male releases sperm to fertilize the eggs as they enter. Then daddy seahorse incubates them for 24 days until the babies are born!

Cool right!?

Anyway, this past weekend I was talking to young moms in different stages of pregnancy or post pregnancy and I heard something that kinda flipped my thinking a bit. One mom said she actually ENJOYED giving birth (I know…what!?!?) because it made her feel powerful, accomplished, and that she was strong enough to endure and conquer this really hard and scary thing. And she told me she wanted to do it again just to feel that feeling once more.

That statement blew me away and I kinda haven’t been able to stop thinking about it. I mean, I live my life in challenges at a time, and the way she put it, kinda spoke to me??? I mean, the whole thing still terrifies me though and I hate pain. I die at period cramps. Yeah, I’m the weakest when it comes to pain tolerance when it’s not of the workout kind 😅

Anyway, to all the women who have done it, you are the true ✨Wonder Women✨!

Thanks to my amazing friend @wendyslookbook for the Wonder Woman outfit transition idea! I’m wearing @popflex_active Tropicana and then changed into a cute beach set I found on ASOS. It was so scary throwing the outfit because it was super windy on Bora Bora and I thought my outfit would land in the ocean. Thank goodness it did not!

♥️Cassey

It’s interesting how people ask when you’re gonna have kids as if it’s actually in your control.

I have multiple friends who have dealt with devastating infertility issues and miscarriages, and honestly I did not know how common these things were until social media gave women an easier place to openly share their stories. My mom had a miscarriage, lots of trouble getting pregnant and had to use Chinese herbs to help her conceive.

So even though right now I’m struggling with the whole “do I want to be a mother” thing - who’s to say that if and when both @samlivits and I decide yes, that I actually can???

I’m in my 30s, I have no idea about the quality or quantity of my eggs, my mom had infertility issues, and to be completely honest with you, my menstrual cycles are also longer than the average woman and they are irregular (they have been since high school when I was training intensely for tennis).

I’m thinking of visiting a clinic to get a check up on my fertility status. The more information the better. I’m very curious. But also…if I’m gonna do it, I say, Sam has to do it too!

What’s been your experience with trying? (I have so much to learn!!!)

♥️Cassey

UGH. I love cheesecake so much and I wish I could eat it everyday (but lactose intolerance 😅).

Anyway, my love for desserts primes me for adventurous recipe testing and that’s why I am so excited to be partnering with @housefoodsamerica to come up with fun and creative recipes using TOFU - the perfect blank slate that can be incorporated into most recipes to give a protein boost! #ad

This time I challenged myself to make a healthy dessert smoothie. The best part? Because it’s made with @housefoodsamerica Tofu, it's packed with protein and would make for a great post-workout smoothie to help rebuild and re-fuel my muscles! 💪

It is SOOOOOO GOOOOOD!!!! I made @samlivits try it and he loved it too!

🍓Strawberry Cheesecake Smoothie:

½ 16 oz block of soft tofu from @housefoodsamerica 
½ c frozen strawberries
½ c frozen bananas
¼ c coconut milk 

Macros: 239 cals, 28g carbs, 8g fat, 13g protein

📺 LIVE WORKOUT + COOKING DEMO:

I’m so excited about this recipe that I want to make this for you LIVE! I’m thinking we start out with a 20 min crazy ab workout at 9AM PST on Tuesday July 20, and then afterwards we can chill and make this post workout smoothie together.

OMG so excited. Are you coming?! 🤓

Go get your ingredients now so we can make it live together on Tuesday!

♥️Cassey

When it comes to picking new products to add to my shop, the 3 most important questions are:

1️⃣ Is it functional AND cute?
2️⃣ Is it innovative?
3️⃣ Does it add value to a fitness girl’s life?

As a baseline, the answer has to be yes to all 3.

Look it’d be easy to match the fabric of a new @popflex_active collection to a scrunchie, but I felt like these little guys have so much more potential! Did some research and discovered that the inner “tube” area of the scrunchie could be converted into a usable pocket!

Omg.

Sometimes I wear a scrunchie on my wrist just for fashion purposes but now, it can hold stuff!?!? YES YES YES!

Couldn’t find one that I loved, so as things go in my life, I made one for myself! Oh and there’s some for you too on popflexactive.com! 😉

And yes that’s a matching headband in the same vegan velvet suede material. Cuz duh. EVERYTHING MUST MATCH!!!

pLiÉ sQuAtS 4 LyFe ✌️ Thank you for all of your thoughtful messages after writing about my confusion towards motherhood. I seriously thought I was alone in this but apparently NOT! Wow. We need to talk about this stuff more. So many women are made to feel bad for a lack of enthusiasm towards kids or not wanting kids at all when the reality is, there are so many TYPES of women out there. I mean obviously right? But not so obvious 😅

I’m grateful that you received my post with genuine understanding. I’m currently on a personal journey of navigating this space and am actually planning mini girl time dates with friends to really talk this one out.

Oh! Also - I noticed that a higher percentage of Asian and Indian women reaching out on this topic saying they felt the same neutralness towards motherhood. Totally hypothesizing, but could it be something specifically related to Asian and Indian American female children who were raised by immigrant parents who were hyper focused our academic and career related success in a new country!?!?

Need to dive deeper.

♥️Cassey

Honeymoons are supposed to be the start of the next phase of life between a couple. And I have to be honest with you. I’m scared.

When @samlivits and I went on our very first date in college, he said “I’d make a really good dad.” 😅 I obviously wasn’t ready to talk such things in between mid terms and research papers. Plus, I had barely just been given “permission” to date by my mom!

When our relationship got more serious, Sam brought up the idea of marriage. I didn’t feel ready so I kept telling him “oh a few more years” every year. I kept delaying it because I didn’t feel like my career was where I wanted it to be. Eventually he proposed 9 years into our relationship and surprised the living daylights outta me in Kauai! Even though I thought I wasn’t ready, it didn’t matter because it unlocked a new level of love in our relationship that I hadn’t felt before.

Now here we are 3 years into our marriage, we finally went on our honeymoon, and that thing Sam said to me in college 13 years ago is a topic that is no longer avoidable. And I’m still scared.

Every day after the wedding Sam would ask me “so when are we having a baby?” and I’d say “oh a couple years.” Same story. I didn’t feel ready because my career wasn’t where I wanted it to be.

I am terrified to tell you this because it’s probably one of the most sensitive things I’ve ever opened up about. It’s probably one of the most unrelatable too.

Unlike all the women I grew up around, having a baby is something they just innately knew they wanted. Me? I don’t know if it’s because of the way I was brought up (super academic + career focused) or if there’s something less “feminine” about me, but I can’t find that internal desire for motherhood. 

To be clear, it’s not that I hate kids or absolutely do not want to become a mother - I’m struggling with the lack of that “natural calling” for motherhood that so many women seem to have. Where is mine?

It’s weird because I’ve always been passion-driven. I follow my heart and it always shows me the right path. But with this, my heart hasn’t spoken up yet and I don’t want to regret missing out on this life experience.

♥️Cassey

Was playing around with weightless exercises on the honeymoon & OMG. Discovered the intensity of a new move I call “tricep pushaways”.

💀

It’s amazing how effective our bodies can be as a weight when we work it against gravity and put it in new, challenging positions. It looks deceptive, but it works. Like crazy.

And look, I’m all for dumbbells and machines (I weight lift in addition to Pilates as well) but I’m NOT FOR people dissing other practices they have not tried! Not into narrow mindedness when the world of movement is so vast and colorful!

♥️Cassey

node.text:
Standing abs. A great thing to try if crunching, sit-upping, and planking just aren’t doing it for your back!

Giving you guys isometric core options based on your level! To make it harder, you can also increase the weight above your head and/or stand on a bosu ball!

What’s an isometric exercise?

It’s an exercise that places tension or work on the muscles you’re focusing on (in this case abs) without shortening or lengthening that muscle group (no crunch up or down). The constant tension is great for endurance, strengthening, and stabilizing of the muscles you’re focusing on! Planks, side planks, and earthquakes are of this category! That’s why Pilates people always have such strong cores.

♥️Cassey

Swipe to the end for the Squat Test in lime!

As you can see the new ButterSoft Compress fabric from @popflex_active doesn’t become more transparent the lower I get into my squat, which is a common issue with active bottoms, especially in lighter colors. But be aware that it CAN still happen in black.

I taught a class once in cheap Forever 21 black leggings (no undies) and let’s just say I’m lucky Sam was there that day because he gave me his hoodie to wrap around…😬😬😬 WHO KNOWS HOW MANY TIMES I’VE WORN THAT LEGGING BEFORE AT THE GYM OMG.

Now of course don’t go around wearing thick lace panties in red with lighter colored leggings. Get yourself a seamless lasercut nude panty/thong or go totally commando which is what I usually do, plus it is way more comfortable! Try it!

Anyway I’m in love with these shots that @jackelynho took at the Tropicana shoot! Like howwww did my little sister become a literal fashion photog like it’s NBD. What. I still shoot using my iPhone pretty exclusively.

♥️Cassey
